<li id="cite_note-kroll82-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-kroll82_24-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-kroll82_24-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-kroll82_24-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-kroll82_24-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-kroll82_24-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal"><a href="/wiki/Jack_Kroll" title="Jack Kroll">Jack Kroll</a> (1982). "A magnificent life of Gandhi". <i><a href="/wiki/Newsweek" title="Newsweek">Newsweek</a></i> (13 December 1982): 60.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGandhi+%28film%29&amp;rft.atitle=A+magnificent+life+of+Gandhi&amp;rft.au=Jack+Kroll&amp;rft.aulast=Jack+Kroll&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=13+December+1982&amp;rft.jtitle=Newsweek&amp;rft.pages=60&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Kroll (1982, p. 60) mentions advocacy of <a href="/wiki/Alec_Guinness" title="Alec Guinness">Alec Guinness</a>, <a href="/wiki/John_Hurt" title="John Hurt">John Hurt</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Dustin_Hoffman" title="Dustin Hoffman">Dustin Hoffman</a>, and quotes Attenborough as stating that "At one point Paramount actually said they'd give me the money if <a href="/wiki/Richard_Burton" title="Richard Burton">Richard Burton</a> could play Gandhi."</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-krollkingsley-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-krollkingsley_26-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See <span class="citation journal">Jack Kroll (1982). "To be or not to be... Gandhi". <i><a href="/wiki/Newsweek" title="Newsweek">Newsweek</a> [US edition]</i> (13 December 1982): 63.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGandhi+%28film%29&amp;rft.atitle=To+be+or+not+to+be...+Gandhi&amp;rft.au=Jack+Kroll&amp;rft.aulast=Jack+Kroll&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=13+December+1982&amp;rft.jtitle=Newsweek+%5BUS+edition%5D&amp;rft.pages=63&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> â "Born <a href="/wiki/Krishna_Bhanji" title="Krishna Bhanji" class="mw-redirect">Krishna Bhanji</a>, Kingsley changed his name when he became an actor: the Kingsley comes from his paternal grandfather, who became a successful spice trader in East Africa and was known as King Clove."</span></li>
